Lift - Class in liftProblemCode
This is an entity that stores the state of the lift - we store things like
the current floor
the direction it is moving in
the lift number - a simple character lift identifier
the list of queued floors for the lift
the next positioning floor for the lift
Lift(String) - Constructor for class liftProblemCode.Lift
Constructor to create a lift, a visual control, and we assume that - the lift starts at floor zero, - has no queued floors - is not moving - an identifier for the lift.
lift - Variable in class liftProblemCode.LiftThread
Lift - a private member reference to the lift that this thread is controlling the movement of.

liftProblemCode - package liftProblemCode
 
LiftProgramRunner - Class in liftProblemCode
This is the main class - its role is to kick off 3 sets of threads - one for the floors waiting another set for the various lifts, along with their identifiers a lift chooser that looks at the state of play and allocates lifts.
